1
00:00:03,838 --> 00:00:07,775
(Minseok) ⟨I was chased out of a South Korean chaebol family after being accused of embezzlement→

2
00:00:08,175 --> 00:00:14,215
In despair, he met Momoko, a doctor at the clinic, and fell in love ⟩

3
00:00:14,548 --> 00:00:18,052
⟨Meanwhile, my Korean mother and brother suddenly came to Japan⟩

4
00:00:18,085 --> 00:00:19,520
>> Korean

5
00:00:19,887 --> 00:00:22,890
(Minseok) ⟨He has announced that he will close the hotel in Tokyo⟩

6
00:00:25,893 --> 00:00:27,828
(Minseok) ⟨To protect the hotel→

7
00:00:27,895 --> 00:00:30,398
I decided to quit on my own, but...⟩

8
00:00:36,404 --> 00:00:39,407
(Minseok) Everything is okay now.

9
00:00:40,908 --> 00:00:43,344
⟨Thanks to my brother who believed in me→

10
00:00:43,411 --> 00:00:45,846
I thought everything was resolved ⟩

11
00:00:45,913 --> 00:00:47,915
⟨but…⟩

12
00:00:54,922 --> 00:00:57,358
(Momoko) Minseok-san, stay strong!

13
00:00:57,425 --> 00:00:59,427
Mr. Minseok!

14
00:01:02,430 --> 00:01:06,367
(footsteps)

15
00:01:12,873 --> 00:01:14,875
(sound of door closing)

16
00:01:17,878 --> 00:01:23,818
(Momoko) Hahaha...｡

17
00:01:23,884 --> 00:01:26,320
(footsteps)

18
00:01:26,387 --> 00:01:28,322
(Takuto) Momoko!

19
00:01:28,389 --> 00:01:29,824
Are you okay?

20
00:01:29,890 --> 00:01:32,827
(Momoko) Min-seok... Min-seok was stabbed and his mother told him.

21
00:01:32,893 --> 00:01:35,830
I was unconscious and couldn't stop the bleeding...

22
00:01:35,896 --> 00:01:39,333
(Takuto) Calm down and take a deep breath.

23
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:43,337
(Momoko) Minseok was stabbed by his mother.

24
00:01:43,404 --> 00:01:47,842
My brother was also taken in for questioning.

25
00:01:47,908 --> 00:01:49,844
(Takuto) What's going on?

26
00:01:49,910 --> 00:01:51,846
(sound of door opening)

27
00:01:51,912 --> 00:01:53,347
(peach) Mr.

28
00:01:53,414 --> 00:01:58,853
>> We are doing everything we can, but the wound is deep and there is significant damage to the liver.

29
00:01:58,919 --> 00:02:01,856
I urgently need a living liver transplant →

30
00:02:01,922 --> 00:02:03,791
Do you have family members who can help?

31
00:02:03,858 --> 00:02:06,794
Preferably a blood relative.

32
00:02:06,861 --> 00:02:09,296
(Momoko) Blood relatives...｡

33
00:02:09,363 --> 00:02:11,799
(Doctor) If you are waiting for a donor other than your family →

34
00:02:11,866 --> 00:02:14,802
Procedures may also take some time.

35
00:02:14,869 --> 00:02:19,306
Until then, I will be connected with a liver support device →

36
00:02:19,373 --> 00:02:21,876
We cannot guarantee that you will be saved.

37
00:02:23,377 --> 00:02:25,880
(Momoko) That's it...

38
00:02:28,883 --> 00:02:30,384
(Takuto) It's okay.

39
00:02:32,386 --> 00:02:34,321
I'll do something.

40
00:02:34,388 --> 00:02:37,892
Momoko, stay by Minchok's side.

41
00:02:39,393 --> 00:02:40,828
(Peach) Takuto.

42
00:02:40,895 --> 00:02:54,842
♪～

43
00:02:54,909 --> 00:02:57,344
(Doctor) [We cannot guarantee that you will be saved]

44
00:02:57,411 --> 00:03:21,302
♪～

45
00:03:21,368 --> 00:03:23,304
(Peach) Takuto.

46
00:03:23,370 --> 00:03:34,381
♪～

47
00:03:37,384 --> 00:03:39,320
>> \I'm coming in/ \Please/

48
00:03:39,386 --> 00:03:41,388
(All) Ichi ni San.

49
00:03:44,892 --> 00:03:49,830
(Sound of electrocardiograph)

50
00:03:49,897 --> 00:03:51,832
(Doctor) The entire liver will be removed for transplantation.

51
00:03:51,899 --> 00:03:53,834
Thank you very much. (All of us) Thank you.

52
00:03:53,901 --> 00:03:56,337
(Doctor) Cooper Sessi. >> \Sessi Gauze/

53
00:03:56,403 --> 00:04:08,349
♪～

54
00:04:18,359 --> 00:04:21,362
(sound of door opening)

55
00:04:24,865 --> 00:04:27,801
The surgery was completed successfully.

56
00:04:27,868 --> 00:04:31,805
(Momoko) Ah, thank you.

57
00:04:31,872 --> 00:04:34,875
>>The rest depends on your own efforts.

58
00:04:36,877 --> 00:04:38,812
(Momoko) Ah, good!

59
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:42,816
>> Excuse me. (Momoko) Ah...｡

60
00:04:42,883 --> 00:04:44,818
Ah...｡

61
00:04:44,885 --> 00:04:46,820
(Takuto) Momoko It's from here.

62
00:04:46,887 --> 00:04:48,822
There's no point in it if you collapse.

63
00:04:48,889 --> 00:04:50,891
(Momoko) Yes.

64
00:04:58,899 --> 00:05:08,275
(Sound of electrocardiograph)

65
00:05:08,342 --> 00:05:10,277
(Momoko) Huh. (Sound of electrocardiograph)

66
00:05:10,344 --> 00:05:18,285
(Sound of electrocardiograph)

67
00:05:18,352 --> 00:05:20,788
(Momoko) Minseok-san.

68
00:05:20,854 --> 00:05:23,290
Teacher, I woke up!

69
00:05:23,357 --> 00:05:27,294
(Doctor) Kim Min-seok, do you understand?

70
00:05:27,361 --> 00:05:29,363
Kim Min Seok.

71
00:05:31,365 --> 00:05:33,300
I had organ transplant surgery →

72
00:05:33,367 --> 00:05:36,804
You will be staying in a private room for severe cases for a while.

73
00:05:36,870 --> 00:05:40,307
Because the hematoma is pressing on a thick bundle of nerves →

74
00:05:40,374 --> 00:05:43,310
I think it will be difficult to walk at first →

75
00:05:43,377 --> 00:05:45,379
Let's do our best in rehabilitation.

76
00:05:47,381 --> 00:05:49,316
trying to say something

77
00:05:49,383 --> 00:05:51,819
what?

78
00:05:51,885 --> 00:05:55,823
(Minseok) She is...

79
00:05:55,889 --> 00:05:59,393
Was it okay?

80
00:06:01,395 --> 00:06:03,263
>> It's okay.

81
00:06:03,330 --> 00:06:06,834
You were by my side the whole time.

82
00:06:11,839 --> 00:06:13,841
(Minseok) Good.

83
00:06:32,359 --> 00:06:33,794
>> Korean

84
00:06:33,861 --> 00:06:35,863
(sound of handcuffs being removed)

85
00:06:48,876 --> 00:06:50,878
(Eri) Poor person.

86
00:06:54,882 --> 00:06:57,818
Me and you too→

87
00:06:57,885 --> 00:07:02,322
I couldn't get what I wanted most.

88
00:07:02,389 --> 00:07:04,758
So somewhere→

89
00:07:04,825 --> 00:07:08,328
I felt like I understood how you felt.

90
00:07:11,331 --> 00:07:16,270
(Eri) But you did something that can't be undone.

91
00:07:16,336 --> 00:07:19,339
Even though you've come this far, you still haven't noticed.

92
00:07:21,842 --> 00:07:24,845
A really pitiful person.

93
00:07:27,347 --> 00:07:29,349
Goodbye.

94
00:07:34,855 --> 00:07:36,356
Korean

95
00:07:41,862 --> 00:07:44,798
(Momoko) Also, an eye mask and towel.

96
00:07:44,865 --> 00:07:48,802
Oh, and this is the required smartphone charger.

97
00:07:48,869 --> 00:07:51,805
This is from the director.

98
00:07:51,872 --> 00:07:54,308
A crossword puzzle to kill time.

99
00:07:54,374 --> 00:07:57,811
(Minseok) Even something like that? thank you.

100
00:07:57,878 --> 00:08:01,882
(Momoko) It seems that having this will make your stay in the hospital a lot more satisfying.

101
00:08:03,817 --> 00:08:07,754
(Minseok) Momoko-san, are you okay with taking time off from work?

102
00:08:07,821 --> 00:08:12,259
(Momoko) The director was also worried and told me to stay by Minseok's side.

103
00:08:12,326 --> 00:08:15,829
Everyone is waiting for Minseok.

104
00:08:17,831 --> 00:08:22,269
Me too, until Minseok regains consciousness →

105
00:08:22,336 --> 00:08:24,838
I didn't feel like I was alive.

106
00:08:27,841 --> 00:08:32,779
(Minseok) While I was sleeping, I had a dream about my father.

107
00:08:32,846 --> 00:08:35,282
(Momoko) Korean? (Minseok) Yes.

108
00:08:35,349 --> 00:08:40,287
When my father collapsed, he was trying to say something to me →

109
00:08:40,354 --> 00:08:42,789
Even though I'm desperately trying to convey something →

110
00:08:42,856 --> 00:08:45,792
I didn't understand.

111
00:08:45,859 --> 00:08:48,295
A dream at that time.

112
00:08:48,362 --> 00:08:50,797
In the end, what do you want to say even in your dreams?

113
00:08:50,864 --> 00:08:53,300
I didn't understand though.

114
00:08:53,367 --> 00:08:54,801
(knock)

115
00:08:54,868 --> 00:08:56,803
(Momoko) Yes.

116
00:08:56,870 --> 00:09:00,807
(Takuto) Yo, you look good.

117
00:09:00,874 --> 00:09:02,809
Mincheok's brother →

118
00:09:02,876 --> 00:09:04,745
They say things like “Get the best room”→

119
00:09:04,811 --> 00:09:07,247
I prepared it specially here.

120
00:09:07,314 --> 00:09:09,249
(Minseok) Ah... (Takuto) It's me.

121
00:09:09,316 --> 00:09:11,251
(Minseok) Thank you.

122
00:09:11,318 --> 00:09:15,255
(Momoko) Takuto is so condescending.

123
00:09:15,322 --> 00:09:17,758
(Takuto) Desa→

124
00:09:17,824 --> 00:09:22,329
Actually, there's someone I need to meet.

125
00:09:36,843 --> 00:09:38,845
(Takuto) Sorry to have kept you waiting.

126
00:09:55,862 --> 00:09:57,864
(Excellent) Photo.

127
00:10:00,367 --> 00:10:02,369
(Minseok) Why?

128
00:10:04,871 --> 00:10:08,809
(Takuto) The person who transplanted organs to Minchok was →

129
00:10:08,875 --> 00:10:10,877
It was my father.

130
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:14,881
(Minseok) Huh?

131
00:10:17,384 --> 00:10:20,887
No, it shouldn't be like that...

132
00:10:22,889 --> 00:10:24,825
Because at that time...

133
00:10:24,891 --> 00:10:27,327
〔father! father! ]

134
00:10:27,394 --> 00:10:28,895
〔father! ]

135
00:10:30,897 --> 00:10:33,333
(Takuto) 23 years ago, Mincheok's parents →

136
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:36,903
I realized this when I looked at the medical records from the time of the accident.

137
00:10:40,407 --> 00:10:44,911
(Takuto's voice) Dad's medical record states the hospital he was transferred to.

138
00:10:46,913 --> 00:10:49,349
Mincheok didn't even attend the funeral →

139
00:10:49,416 --> 00:10:53,854
I was worried that I didn't even know where the grave was.

140
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:58,425
At the hospital I was transferred to, I was asked to tell me the story of that time.

141
00:11:02,929 --> 00:11:04,865
(Minseok) Why?

142
00:11:07,367 --> 00:11:11,805
>> Can we talk for a moment?

143
00:11:11,872 --> 00:11:27,821
♪～

144
00:11:27,888 --> 00:11:29,890
It was bad to stay silent.

145
00:11:32,893 --> 00:11:36,897
I know that I'm not allowed to come out and apologize now.

146
00:11:41,902 --> 00:11:43,904
(Minseok) I'm a little confused...

147
00:11:46,907 --> 00:11:48,909
(Minseok) What do you mean?

148
00:11:51,411 --> 00:11:54,848
>> 23 years ago →

149
00:11:54,915 --> 00:11:57,918
After being seriously injured in an accident...

150
00:12:01,421 --> 00:12:04,291
I can no longer walk →

151
00:12:04,357 --> 00:12:08,295
Pretend you're dead →

152
00:12:08,361 --> 00:12:10,864
I wanted to let go of Teru.

153
00:12:13,867 --> 00:12:15,869
(Minseok) Why?

154
00:12:17,370 --> 00:12:20,807
>> To live with light→

155
00:12:20,874 --> 00:12:25,312
I didn't know where to turn for help.

156
00:12:25,378 --> 00:12:27,881
I also had my own weaknesses.

157
00:12:29,883 --> 00:12:33,320
(Minseok) So→

158
00:12:33,386 --> 00:12:36,389
Did you leave me with my father?

159
00:12:38,892 --> 00:12:42,829
(Yu's voice) If it's Jeonghoon who I trust the most →

160
00:12:42,896 --> 00:12:45,398
I thought I could entrust the light to you.

161
00:12:50,904 --> 00:12:53,406
It was really bad.

162
00:12:59,913 --> 00:13:03,283
I've wanted to visit you many times.

163
00:13:03,350 --> 00:13:07,287
Two years have passed since the accident →

164
00:13:07,354 --> 00:13:09,856
I've been to Seoul.

165
00:13:12,859 --> 00:13:18,365
But I couldn't call out.

166
00:13:20,867 --> 00:13:24,804
Teru is in a new place →

167
00:13:24,871 --> 00:13:28,875
Trying to live as Kim Min Seok...

168
00:13:31,378 --> 00:13:36,316
Because I was desperately trying to live as Kim Min-seok.

169
00:13:36,383 --> 00:13:40,387
I thought I couldn't get in the way.

170
00:13:42,389 --> 00:13:44,324
Whatever you say will be an excuse.

171
00:13:44,391 --> 00:13:47,327
But →

172
00:13:47,394 --> 00:13:52,832
Not even a day, not even a second →

173
00:13:52,899 --> 00:13:56,336
I am Teruno...

174
00:13:56,403 --> 00:13:59,339
(Minseok) I am →

175
00:13:59,406 --> 00:14:01,408
This is Kim Min-seok.

176
00:14:04,344 --> 00:14:07,781
I can't go back to Teru Aoki now.

177
00:14:07,847 --> 00:14:14,287
You are my little self →

178
00:14:14,354 --> 00:14:19,359
How much I wanted to see my deceased parents...

179
00:14:21,361 --> 00:14:26,800
How lonely I felt→

180
00:14:26,866 --> 00:14:29,302
Have you never thought about it?

181
00:14:29,369 --> 00:14:40,313
♪～

182
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:43,817
(Minseok) Thank you for saving my life.

183
00:14:43,883 --> 00:14:46,386
But now...

184
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:53,326
(Minseok) I don't know what to say.

185
00:14:53,393 --> 00:14:55,328
Sorry.

186
00:14:55,395 --> 00:15:06,273
♪～

187
00:15:06,339 --> 00:15:12,345
(cry)

188
00:15:19,653 --> 00:15:21,588
(sound of door opening)

189
00:15:21,655 --> 00:15:23,657
(Momoko) Minseok-san.

190
00:15:27,661 --> 00:15:31,598
(Minseok) Thank you, Takuto-san.

191
00:15:31,665 --> 00:15:33,600
(Takuto) Who is your father?

192
00:15:33,667 --> 00:15:35,669
(Minseok) I talked.

193
00:15:37,170 --> 00:15:42,676
But my father is a Korean father.

194
00:15:44,177 --> 00:15:46,613
My life was saved by everyone.

195
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:51,618
I will do my best in rehabilitation and get well soon.

196
00:15:51,685 --> 00:15:53,687
(Physical Therapist) I'll bend it slightly.

197
00:15:59,192 --> 00:16:01,127
(Physical therapist) Do you feel uncomfortable?

198
00:16:01,194 --> 00:16:03,129
(Minseok) It's okay. (Physical therapist) Yeah.

199
00:16:03,196 --> 00:16:05,065
(Kazami) Would you like to eat the pudding I gave you?

200
00:16:05,131 --> 00:16:08,068
(Momoko) Ah, I'm going to Yamashiro Memorial Hospital.

201
00:16:08,134 --> 00:16:10,070
(Mika) Huh, Momo-chan-sensei, how about some pudding?

202
00:16:10,136 --> 00:16:12,072
(Momoko) Ah, Mika-chan, you can eat.

203
00:16:12,138 --> 00:16:15,575
I was thinking of delivering the children's letters to Min-seok.

204
00:16:15,642 --> 00:16:18,078
>> I'll bring it later because I'm on my way home.

205
00:16:18,144 --> 00:16:20,080
(Momoko) Ah, no, but...

206
00:16:20,146 --> 00:16:24,584
(Kazami) Ah, Momo-chan, then she was transferred to Yamashiro→

207
00:16:24,651 --> 00:16:28,588
Could you please ask me how my patient is doing?

208
00:16:28,655 --> 00:16:31,157
(Momoko) Okay, then I'll go!

209
00:16:32,659 --> 00:16:34,594
>> Even I can do that much.

210
00:16:34,661 --> 00:16:36,596
Mika-chan.

211
00:16:36,663 --> 00:16:39,666
It's a stable insensitivity. >> Huh, what do you mean?

212
00:16:50,176 --> 00:16:52,112
Do you want to take a break?

213
00:16:52,178 --> 00:16:54,681
(Minseok) Ah, it's still okay.

214
00:16:55,682 --> 00:16:58,618
Are we causing any inconvenience to you?

215
00:16:58,685 --> 00:17:01,621
(Natsume) No, after the deputy manager left →

216
00:17:01,688 --> 00:17:04,557
Who do you think is the least energetic?

217
00:17:04,624 --> 00:17:07,060
(Minseok) Who is it?

218
00:17:07,127 --> 00:17:09,562
>> I'm the manager. (Minseok) Huh?

219
00:17:09,629 --> 00:17:13,066
(Mizushima) Well… Look, manager.

220
00:17:13,133 --> 00:17:17,570
In Korea →

221
00:17:17,637 --> 00:17:21,574
I heard that this kind of thing is common for visits, so yes.

222
00:17:21,641 --> 00:17:23,576
(Minseok) Thank you.

223
00:17:23,643 --> 00:17:27,580
>> Yeah, I'm in trouble if you don't fill that hole in my job as soon as possible.

224
00:17:27,647 --> 00:17:29,649
I don't know.

225
00:17:31,651 --> 00:17:33,586
(Physical Therapist) Se-no.

226
00:17:33,653 --> 00:17:35,588
(Minseok) Ah...

227
00:17:35,655 --> 00:17:39,592
(Physical Therapist) Put your butt out in front of you right away.

228
00:17:39,659 --> 00:17:42,095
Ah! (Minseok) Sorry.

229
00:17:42,162 --> 00:17:45,098
>>Okay, let's finish here for today.

230
00:17:45,165 --> 00:18:10,690
♪～

231
00:18:12,192 --> 00:18:14,194
Korean

232
00:19:23,696 --> 00:19:26,199
Korean

233
00:19:44,717 --> 00:19:47,220
(Kyunhua) Huh…｡

234
00:21:09,168 --> 00:21:11,170
Ha!

235
00:22:51,704 --> 00:23:05,651
♪～

236
00:23:42,688 --> 00:23:44,690
〔Yeah〕

237
00:23:46,192 --> 00:23:48,194
(Junghoon) [Hahaha…]

238
00:24:20,660 --> 00:24:22,161
(sound of closing diary)

239
00:25:21,654 --> 00:25:23,656
(cry)

240
00:25:43,175 --> 00:25:57,623
(cry)

241
00:25:57,690 --> 00:26:00,626
The wound is healing well.

242
00:26:00,693 --> 00:26:02,628
(Minseok) It's all thanks to you, teacher.

243
00:26:02,695 --> 00:26:04,697
thank you.

244
00:26:08,701 --> 00:26:12,138
>> I would like him to continue to work hard on his rehabilitation even after being discharged from the hospital.→

245
00:26:12,204 --> 00:26:16,208
There's one thing I have to tell you.

246
00:26:18,711 --> 00:26:23,149
As the pressure is prolonged and the paralysis is becoming fixed →

247
00:26:23,215 --> 00:26:27,153
Recovery of walking may be difficult.

248
00:26:27,219 --> 00:26:29,155
(Minseok) Huh?

249
00:26:29,221 --> 00:26:34,160
>> In that case, it can also be used in daily life such as excretion and bathing →

250
00:26:34,226 --> 00:26:36,729
I think you will need assistance.

251
00:26:40,733 --> 00:26:45,738
(Minseok) But if you do rehabilitation, you'll be fine, right?

252
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:51,677
>> Honestly, looking at what's going on now →

253
00:26:51,744 --> 00:26:54,747
The situation is indescribable.

254
00:26:59,719 --> 00:27:02,722
(Takuto) Momoko, can you open it? (Momoko) Yeah, OK.

255
00:27:05,391 --> 00:27:07,593
Please be careful on the stairs. (Takuto) Thank you.

256
00:27:07,927 --> 00:27:10,363
Let's go, Minseok. (Minseok) Yes. (Takuto) Good.

257
00:27:10,429 --> 00:27:11,931
(Momoko) Yay!

258
00:27:14,433 --> 00:27:16,869
Yes, OK. (Takuto) Well then, I'll put down the minchok.

259
00:27:16,936 --> 00:27:19,372
(Minseok) Thank you. (Takuto) Okay, I'll go slowly.

260
00:27:19,438 --> 00:27:21,374
Se-no.

261
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:23,876
Good.

262
00:27:23,943 --> 00:27:25,945
(Minseok) Thank you.

263
00:27:30,950 --> 00:27:32,885
(Takuto) OK. (Minseok) Thank you.

264
00:27:32,952 --> 00:27:36,389
(Knock) (Momoko) Konkonkon Can I come in?

265
00:27:36,455 --> 00:27:38,457
(Haru) Shi~!

266
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:43,396
(Takuto) It's good.

267
00:27:43,462 --> 00:27:45,398
Mincheok, don't look behind you yet.

268
00:27:45,464 --> 00:27:46,899
(Minseok) Ah.

269
00:27:46,966 --> 00:27:49,402
(Takuto) Not yet, not yet.

270
00:27:49,468 --> 00:27:51,904
Good.

271
00:27:51,971 --> 00:27:54,907
Se-no! (Momoko) Let's go!

272
00:27:54,974 --> 00:27:59,979
(All) Minseok-san, welcome back!

273
00:28:03,482 --> 00:28:05,418
yeah? >> Mr. Minseok?

274
00:28:05,484 --> 00:28:07,353
(Minseok) Ah...｡

275
00:28:07,420 --> 00:28:10,356
I was surprised and happy.

276
00:28:10,423 --> 00:28:13,359
(Takuto) Great success everyone!

277
00:28:13,426 --> 00:28:17,363
(All) Yay!

278
00:28:17,430 --> 00:28:19,865
(Child) Is your foot okay? (Minseok) Yeah, it's okay.

279
00:28:19,932 --> 00:28:22,868
>> Wheelchair looks cool. (Minseok) Eh, really?

280
00:28:22,935 --> 00:28:24,870
(Takuto) That's cool. (Child) Yeah.

281
00:28:24,937 --> 00:28:27,873
(Kyoko) This much? (Chica) Kyoko-chan is a little normal.

282
00:28:27,940 --> 00:28:30,876
(Kyoko) Normal? (Momoko) Ah, I understand, Chika-chan.

283
00:28:30,943 --> 00:28:32,878
Do you want me to do it like Minseok?

284
00:28:32,945 --> 00:28:34,380
(Chica) Yeah.

285
00:28:34,447 --> 00:28:37,383
(Momoko) Minseok's presentation is special.

286
00:28:37,450 --> 00:28:40,386
(Takuto) Whoa, is it finally my turn?

287
00:28:40,453 --> 00:28:43,889
(Yusuke) Takuto is no good because he has no sense!

288
00:28:43,956 --> 00:28:46,892
(Takuto) Hey, what is NG?

289
00:28:46,959 --> 00:28:49,895
(Minseok) Ah, I'll do it.

290
00:28:49,962 --> 00:28:51,897
Can I come by for a while? Sorry for the back.

291
00:28:51,964 --> 00:28:53,899
(Takuto) Then everyone will pass through Minchok, so spread out.

292
00:28:53,966 --> 00:28:55,901
(Minseok) Take care of your feet. >> Yes.

293
00:28:55,968 --> 00:28:57,470
(Takuto) Let's go.

294
00:29:02,475 --> 00:29:05,911
(Takuto) It looks like it's going to be difficult to get inside.

295
00:29:05,978 --> 00:29:08,848
(Momoko) Ah, then should I have you do it from your side?

296
00:29:08,914 --> 00:29:11,350
I mean, it's about time we redecorated this place.

297
00:29:11,417 --> 00:29:13,352
I originally thought it was small.

298
00:29:13,419 --> 00:29:15,354
>> Yes, that's right.

299
00:29:15,421 --> 00:29:17,356
(Minseok) Sorry for making such a fuss.

300
00:29:17,423 --> 00:29:20,860
(Takuto) What are you talking about? I'm so NG.

301
00:29:20,926 --> 00:29:22,862
Please, Mincheok.

302
00:29:22,928 --> 00:29:25,364
(Minseok) Yes.

303
00:29:25,431 --> 00:29:27,366
(Momoko) Yes, Minseok-san. (Minseok) Thank you.

304
00:29:27,433 --> 00:29:29,435
(Momoko) Where should I start?

305
00:29:31,437 --> 00:29:32,872
Ah, is this it?

306
00:29:32,938 --> 00:29:35,441
(Minseok) Oh, sorry. (Momoko) Yes, please.

307
00:29:44,450 --> 00:29:46,886
(Minseok) Thank you. (Momoko) Yes.

308
00:29:46,952 --> 00:29:48,888
(Minseok) Then... >> Ah, is this it?

309
00:29:48,954 --> 00:29:50,956
(Minseok) Oh, sorry.

310
00:29:56,462 --> 00:29:58,464
(Child) It's home!

311
00:29:59,965 --> 00:30:01,901
(Minseok) Sorry it took so long.

312
00:30:01,967 --> 00:30:06,839
>> It's okay, it's okay, I don't care because I'm the main character! Hey.

313
00:30:06,906 --> 00:30:08,841
Then I'll have it!

314
00:30:08,908 --> 00:30:11,911
(All) Itadakimasu!

315
00:30:15,414 --> 00:30:18,350
(Kyoko) Please do this too. (Momoko) Ah, thank you.

316
00:30:18,417 --> 00:30:19,852
Hey, sister.

317
00:30:19,919 --> 00:30:21,854
Mika-chan, could you please help me out?

318
00:30:21,921 --> 00:30:25,357
(Child: Kazami) Yes, thank you for the meal.

319
00:30:25,424 --> 00:30:27,359
Well done.

320
00:30:27,426 --> 00:30:29,361
(Takuto) This is suspicious.

321
00:30:29,428 --> 00:30:31,363
(Minseok) Should I put down the dishes? >> Yeah.

322
00:30:31,430 --> 00:30:33,365
I will lower it for Minseok-san.

323
00:30:33,432 --> 00:30:35,367
(Minseok) Is it okay? >> Yes!

324
00:30:35,434 --> 00:30:37,369
(Minseok) Thank you.

325
00:30:37,436 --> 00:30:40,372
>> Do you need water for your medicine? I'll bring it to you.

326
00:30:40,439 --> 00:30:43,876
(Minseok) Thank you. (Yusuke) Yeah.

327
00:30:43,943 --> 00:30:46,378
Momo-chan, please add some water. (Momoko) Yes, yes.

328
00:30:46,445 --> 00:30:48,948
(Takuto) He's more considerate than me.

329
00:30:51,450 --> 00:30:54,453
(Momoko) Yes, please. >> Yes. (Momoko) Thank you.

330
00:31:11,904 --> 00:31:13,839
(Minseok) Ah. (Takuto) Yusuke!

331
00:31:13,906 --> 00:31:15,341
(Momoko) Huh!

332
00:31:15,407 --> 00:31:18,844
(Takuto) Is Minchok okay too? Please show me a little.

333
00:31:18,911 --> 00:31:22,348
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

334
00:31:22,414 --> 00:31:24,850
(Minseok) Ah. (Momoko) Minseok! OK?

335
00:31:24,917 --> 00:31:27,853
(Minseok) Yes, Yusuke-kun?

336
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:29,855
>> It's okay.

337
00:31:29,922 --> 00:31:32,858
(Minseok) Ah... (Momoko) Minseok, I'll move it.

338
00:31:32,925 --> 00:31:34,860
(Minseok) Excuse me. (Momoko) Se~no Ugh!

339
00:31:34,927 --> 00:31:37,363
(Minseok) Ah, are you okay? >> An-chan, hold the wheelchair.

340
00:31:37,429 --> 00:31:39,365
Ah, yes. (Takuto) Let's go.

341
00:31:39,431 --> 00:31:41,367
Se-no.

342
00:31:41,433 --> 00:31:43,435
(Minseok) Ah...

343
00:31:45,437 --> 00:31:47,373
Sorry, please grab me.

344
00:31:47,439 --> 00:31:48,874
(Takuto) I'll grab some clothes. (Minseok) Yes.

345
00:31:48,941 --> 00:31:51,877
(Takuto) Se~no. (Momoko) Se~no.

346
00:31:51,944 --> 00:31:53,379
(Takuto) Ah!

347
00:31:53,445 --> 00:31:55,881
(Minseok) Ha ha ha.

348
00:31:55,948 --> 00:32:01,887
Huh… hah hah…｡

349
00:32:01,954 --> 00:32:03,956
I'm sorry.

350
00:32:18,671 --> 00:32:20,172
>> Korean

351
00:32:47,132 --> 00:32:49,568
(Kyoko) What are you looking at?

352
00:32:49,635 --> 00:32:52,071
(Momoko) ``Summary of places you can go with a wheelchair.''

353
00:32:52,137 --> 00:32:55,074
There is something like this.

354
00:32:55,140 --> 00:32:59,144
Clinics also need to be barrier-free.

355
00:33:01,146 --> 00:33:06,085
Ah! It's already that time! Hey~

356
00:33:06,151 --> 00:33:10,656
I was asked to come up with a menu for the children's cafeteria by tomorrow.

357
00:33:12,157 --> 00:33:13,592
>> Momoko.

358
00:33:13,659 --> 00:33:15,594
(Momoko) Huh?

359
00:33:15,661 --> 00:33:19,098
>>If you have any trouble, let me know.

360
00:33:19,164 --> 00:33:20,599
(Momoko) Huh?

361
00:33:20,666 --> 00:33:22,668
>> Big sister, I'll help you.

362
00:33:24,169 --> 00:33:26,672
(Momoko) Yes, thank you.

363
00:33:29,675 --> 00:33:31,610
(sound of door closing)

364
00:33:31,677 --> 00:34:04,076
♪～

365
00:34:04,143 --> 00:34:06,078
(Momoko) That's all for today.

366
00:34:06,145 --> 00:34:08,080
>> Please take care.

367
00:34:08,147 --> 00:34:10,149
(Momoko) Take care.

368
00:34:19,158 --> 00:34:21,593
>> Momo-chan sensei. (Momoko) Ah.

369
00:34:21,660 --> 00:34:25,597
>> I'm amazing.

370
00:34:25,664 --> 00:34:28,600
I had a friend that I was close with in high school →

371
00:34:28,667 --> 00:34:31,603
We always played in groups of three.

372
00:34:31,670 --> 00:34:34,606
Two people other than me have been dating for a long time →

373
00:34:34,673 --> 00:34:37,609
I didn't realize it until they announced that they were getting married.

374
00:34:37,676 --> 00:34:39,111
(Momoko) Um...｡

375
00:34:39,178 --> 00:34:44,049
>> In other words, I'm extremely insensitive.

376
00:34:44,116 --> 00:34:49,054
Momo-chan-sensei was so insensitive that I noticed it→

377
00:34:49,121 --> 00:34:51,623
It's obvious that he's dating Minseok.

378
00:34:56,128 --> 00:35:00,065
It was written on my back that I wanted to go on a date early today.

379
00:35:00,132 --> 00:35:02,067
(Momoko) Sorry.

380
00:35:02,134 --> 00:35:05,070
>> Please go, I'll be back eventually.

381
00:35:05,137 --> 00:35:09,074
(Momoko) Thank you. I will definitely repay this favor...

382
00:35:09,141 --> 00:35:11,076
>> With strawberry daifuku! (Momoko) Thank you!

383
00:35:11,143 --> 00:35:13,579
>> Strawberry Daifuku!

384
00:35:13,645 --> 00:35:16,582
(Kazami) You finally noticed!

385
00:35:16,648 --> 00:35:19,651
This is the limit of insensitivity.

386
00:35:20,652 --> 00:35:22,588
welcome.

387
00:35:22,654 --> 00:35:24,156
(Momoko) Good evening.

388
00:35:30,162 --> 00:35:32,164
(Salesperson) Please excuse me.

389
00:35:39,671 --> 00:35:42,040
(Momoko) Sorry to have kept you waiting. (Minseok) No.

390
00:35:42,107 --> 00:35:45,611
(Momoko) Thank you. >> Please take your time.

391
00:35:49,114 --> 00:35:54,052
(Momoko) Is this a restaurant where the menu is all in French?

392
00:35:54,119 --> 00:35:57,055
(Minseok) Japanese is also available. (Momoko) Good.

393
00:35:57,122 --> 00:36:00,058
(Minseok) What do you want to eat?

394
00:36:00,125 --> 00:36:02,060
There are also many wines.

395
00:36:02,127 --> 00:36:05,564
(Momoko) Wow~ Is it okay?

396
00:36:05,631 --> 00:36:07,132
(Minseok) Of course.

397
00:36:15,140 --> 00:36:17,075
(Momoko) Hmm.

398
00:36:17,142 --> 00:36:20,579
It's a combination of flavors that I've never had before.

399
00:36:20,646 --> 00:36:23,081
What's in this sauce?

400
00:36:23,148 --> 00:36:25,584
Children may also like the taste.

401
00:36:25,651 --> 00:36:27,586
delicious.

402
00:36:27,653 --> 00:36:30,589
Ah, but this is a little too mature.

403
00:36:30,656 --> 00:36:32,591
(Minseok) That was difficult.

404
00:36:32,658 --> 00:36:35,661
(Momoko) I really have to be careful hahaha...｡

405
00:36:37,162 --> 00:36:41,033
Hey, if the earth were to be destroyed tomorrow...

406
00:36:41,099 --> 00:36:43,035
(Minseok) Huh? (Momoko) Minseok finally →

407
00:36:43,101 --> 00:36:45,537
What do you want to eat?

408
00:36:45,604 --> 00:36:47,539
(Minseok) That's sudden.

409
00:36:47,606 --> 00:36:50,042
(Momoko) I always think about this.

410
00:36:50,108 --> 00:36:52,544
(Minseok) Do you have the answer? Momoko's.

411
00:36:52,611 --> 00:36:54,546
(Momoko) Could you please not laugh?

412
00:36:54,613 --> 00:36:56,048
(Minseok) Of course.

413
00:36:56,114 --> 00:37:00,552
(Momoko) I have my sister's usual money-saving recipe.

414
00:37:00,619 --> 00:37:02,554
Come and try this delicious food →

415
00:37:02,621 --> 00:37:05,557
I'm not talking about doing that though. (Minseok) Ah.

416
00:37:05,624 --> 00:37:09,061
(Momoko) The tofu was falling apart and the bean sprouts were falling apart.

417
00:37:09,127 --> 00:37:13,065
It also contains green onions that I grew.

418
00:37:13,131 --> 00:37:17,135
I want to taste each and every one of those things at the end.

419
00:37:18,637 --> 00:37:21,573
Does Minseok have that kind of food too?

420
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:26,578
(Minseok) Ah, I...

421
00:37:26,645 --> 00:37:29,081
(Knock) (Salesperson) Excuse me.

422
00:37:29,147 --> 00:37:32,584
(Minseok) Ah, it's the main thing. (Momoko) It's the main thing.

423
00:37:32,651 --> 00:37:36,154
(Staff) It's grilled beef fillet Chaliapin style.

424
00:37:38,657 --> 00:37:41,026
(Peach) Foreword withdrawn.

425
00:37:41,093 --> 00:37:45,097
This may be the meal you will have on your last day on earth.

426
00:37:50,602 --> 00:37:53,038
(Momoko) This is also really delicious.

427
00:37:53,105 --> 00:37:56,041
(Minseok) I'm glad you like it.

428
00:37:56,108 --> 00:37:58,543
(Momoko) Next I will take care of Minseok →

429
00:37:58,610 --> 00:38:01,113
I'll take you to a delicious restaurant.

430
00:38:08,620 --> 00:38:11,056
(Minseok) Momoko-san.

431
00:38:11,123 --> 00:38:15,560
I came here today because I wanted to talk to you about something.

432
00:38:15,627 --> 00:38:20,565
(Momoko) Yes, what is it?

433
00:38:20,632 --> 00:38:23,635
(Minseok) It's about my body.

434
00:38:25,137 --> 00:38:28,573
I'll be here forever→

435
00:38:28,640 --> 00:38:31,643
You may not be able to walk.

436
00:38:34,646 --> 00:38:39,584
(Minseok) Returned to Korea and continued rehabilitation →

437
00:38:39,651 --> 00:38:42,587
I'm thinking of working at a company.

438
00:38:44,089 --> 00:38:46,525
(Momoko) That's...

439
00:38:46,591 --> 00:38:51,596
(Minseok) I won't be able to see Momoko again.

440
00:38:53,098 --> 00:38:55,534
(Momoko) Huh?

441
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:59,037
(Minseok) When Yusuke fell down at the children's cafeteria →

442
00:38:59,104 --> 00:39:02,541
I can't prevent or help in advance →

443
00:39:02,607 --> 00:39:04,543
It was frustrating.

444
00:39:04,609 --> 00:39:08,046
I also fell down and couldn't get up →

445
00:39:08,113 --> 00:39:12,551
I've caused trouble to everyone.

446
00:39:12,617 --> 00:39:15,554
(Momoko) That wasn't Minseok's fault.

447
00:39:15,620 --> 00:39:17,556
(Minseok) That's not all.

448
00:39:17,622 --> 00:39:21,560
Entering the clinic and setting up the food →

449
00:39:21,626 --> 00:39:24,563
I had to borrow everyone's help.

450
00:39:24,629 --> 00:39:29,568
There were many things I couldn't do and I just apologized.

451
00:39:29,634 --> 00:39:35,073
(Momoko) It's a bad situation to have to apologize for something like that.

452
00:39:35,140 --> 00:39:37,142
Minseok isn't bad.

453
00:39:42,080 --> 00:39:45,517
(Minseok) I am now→

454
00:39:45,584 --> 00:39:49,087
I can't even change my clothes by myself.

455
00:39:51,089 --> 00:39:53,525
Even today, my brother helped me →

456
00:39:53,592 --> 00:39:57,529
I was finally able to get dressed.

457
00:39:57,596 --> 00:39:59,531
(Momoko) That's how prepared I am...

458
00:39:59,598 --> 00:40:03,535
(Minseok) Even in the toilet→

459
00:40:03,602 --> 00:40:06,104
I can't go alone.

460
00:40:08,106 --> 00:40:12,043
But if I go back to Korea →

461
00:40:12,110 --> 00:40:15,547
Still for me →

462
00:40:15,614 --> 00:40:18,617
There are things you can do for the company.

463
00:40:26,124 --> 00:40:30,061
(Minseok) Just now →

464
00:40:30,128 --> 00:40:35,567
The last time we talked about what we wanted to eat →

465
00:40:35,634 --> 00:40:39,137
There was something that came to mind.

466
00:40:41,072 --> 00:40:43,074
(Momoko) What?

467
00:40:45,577 --> 00:40:50,582
(Minseok) Cup ramen I ate by the river with Momoko.

468
00:40:54,085 --> 00:40:56,087
(Minseok) It was a taste I don't want to forget.

469
00:40:58,590 --> 00:41:02,027
But →

470
00:41:02,093 --> 00:41:05,530
I have to take Momoko out →

471
00:41:05,597 --> 00:41:10,535
You can also eat cup ramen and lie down by the river →

472
00:41:10,602 --> 00:41:14,539
You can also ride a jet coaster at the amusement park →

473
00:41:14,606 --> 00:41:18,109
You can't just drop by the children's cafeteria.

474
00:41:25,617 --> 00:41:28,620
(Momoko) It's not like that...

475
00:41:31,122 --> 00:41:34,125
Not because I can do that...

476
00:41:36,628 --> 00:41:39,064
I just→

477
00:41:39,130 --> 00:41:42,133
I want to be with Minseok.

478
00:41:43,635 --> 00:41:48,073
(Minseok) When I meet Momoko-san →

479
00:41:48,139 --> 00:41:52,077
There are only things I want to do but can't do →

480
00:41:52,143 --> 00:41:55,580
Floating in my head→

481
00:41:55,647 --> 00:41:59,584
I'm afraid I'll cause trouble for Momoko.

482
00:41:59,651 --> 00:42:02,153
(Momoko) I don't think so.

483
00:42:03,655 --> 00:42:07,092
(Minseok) I am →

484
00:42:07,158 --> 00:42:11,096
Momoko's life →

485
00:42:11,162 --> 00:42:13,665
I want to support your dreams.

486
00:42:16,167 --> 00:42:20,105
But I can't do that.

487
00:42:20,171 --> 00:42:23,608
(Momoko) Minseok-san, that will never happen.

488
00:42:23,675 --> 00:42:28,613
(Minseok) If you came here today, this is the store→

489
00:42:28,680 --> 00:42:31,182
Because even I was able to enter.

490
00:42:35,687 --> 00:42:39,624
(Minseok) Lastly →

491
00:42:39,691 --> 00:42:45,063
Eating delicious food with Momoko →

492
00:42:45,130 --> 00:42:48,633
It's because I wanted to laugh with you.

493
00:42:53,138 --> 00:42:58,143
(Momoko) I don't want to be separated from Minseok-san.

494
00:43:01,646 --> 00:43:04,649
(Minseok) When I'm with Momoko...

495
00:43:08,653 --> 00:43:11,656
(Minseok) I can't stand myself.

496
00:43:19,164 --> 00:43:21,166
(Minseok) I think it's now.

497
00:43:23,668 --> 00:43:26,605
We can go back to our respective paths.

498
00:43:26,671 --> 00:44:00,572
♪～

499
00:44:00,638 --> 00:44:05,143
>> Are you sure you can go home?

500
00:44:06,645 --> 00:44:08,646
(Minseok) Yes.

501
00:44:10,148 --> 00:44:13,084
What I learned here →

502
00:44:13,151 --> 00:44:16,087
I will utilize this information in the future management of Fungum.

503
00:44:16,154 --> 00:44:18,590
>>Not yet→

504
00:44:18,656 --> 00:44:25,096
I told you that there are many things I haven't taught you.

505
00:44:25,163 --> 00:44:29,100
(Minseok) It was a pleasure working with you all →

506
00:44:29,167 --> 00:44:31,169
